i.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/24/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/24/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/24/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNUXf88AAAABHpmvGQ\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4808354459,\\\"number\\\":9,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Training Memory Leak at various steps\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"While training with a larger batch size, I encounter consistently a OOM issue when the second my train-batch is started, while with lower batch sizes the OOM error happens at various steps between step 3 and 7. What could be the reason for this?\\\\n\\\\nI using the config.yaml as basis with the following adjustments on 4 H100s for the lower batch size:\\\\n\\\\n#!/bin/bash\\\\n\\\\nset -x\\\\n\\\\nexport PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1\\\\n\\\\nMODEL_PATH=Qwen/Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct\\\\n\\\\npython3 -m verl.trainer.main \\\\\\\\\\\\n    config=examples/config.yaml \\\\\\\\\\\\n    worker.actor.model.model_path=${MODEL_PATH} \\\\\\\\\\\\n    trainer.n_gpus_per_node=4 \\\\\\\\\\\\n    data.rollout_batch_size=128 \\\\\\\\\\\\n    worker.rollout.n=20 \\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\n\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T09:00:13Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T09:00:14Z\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9\\\",\\\"comments_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9/comments\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9/events\\\",\\\"labels_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9/labels{/name}\\\",\\\"repository_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1\\\",\\\"reactions\\\":{\\\"total_count\\\":0,\\\"+1\\\":0,\\\"-1\\\":0,\\\"laugh\\\":0,\\\"confused\\\":0,\\\"heart\\\":0,\\\"hooray\\\":0,\\\"rocket\\\":0,\\\"eyes\\\":0,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/repos/mangowhoiscloud/EasyR1/issues/9/reactions\\\"},\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"I_kwDOTNUXf88AAAABHpmqmw\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4808354385,\\\"number\\\":6,\\\"state\\\":\\\"open\\\",\\\"locked\\\":false,\\\"title\\\":\\\"memory need for training Qwen-2.5VL-instruct-3B?\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"as suggested, i use BF16 and training Qwen-2.5VL-instruct-3B on a 48GB L20. To enable bf16 training, I added `torch_dtype: bf16` and `strategy: adamw_bf16` to the `examples/config.yaml` file. However, when I subsequently ran the training command `bash examples/qwen2_5_vl_3b_geo3k_grpo.sh` for the 3B model, I encountered an out-of-memory (OOM) error. I'm using a single L20 GPU with 48GB VRAM. According to the official GitHub project documentation, training the 3B model (BF) should require only 40GB of memory. I'm unclear why this OOM error occurred.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003cimg width=\\\\\\\"909\\\\\\\" height=\\\\\\\"488\\\\\\\" alt=\\\\\\\"Image\\\\\\\" src=\\\\\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2665b497-e084-44fb-a7ca-c8ed666d8be6\\\\\\\" /\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"author_association\\\":\\\"OWNER\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"id\\\":191002565,\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"U_kgDOC2J3xQ\\\",\\\"avatar_url\\\":\\\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/191002565?v=4\\\",\\\"html_url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"gravatar_id\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"User\\\",\\\"site_admin\\\":false,\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud\\\",\\\"events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/events{/privacy}\\\",\\\"following_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/following{/other_user}\\\",\\\"followers_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/followers\\\",\\\"gists_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/gists{/gist_id}\\\",\\\"organizations_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/orgs\\\",\\\"received_events_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/received_events\\\",\\\"repos_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/repos\\\",\\\"starred_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/starred{/owner}{/repo}\\\",\\\"subscriptions_url\\\":\\\"https://api.github.com/users/mangowhoiscloud/subscriptions\\\"},\\\"comments\\\":0,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T09:00:11Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-04T09:00:11Z\\\